## How entries land here

The generic adapter has **no SessionEnd hook**. Memory entries are written
manually. Two recommended rituals:

1. **End of session.** After a meaningful working session, append one entry per
   genuine learning to the right bucket file in `memory/<bucket>/`. Update the
   relevant section above with a one-line index pointer (under ~150 chars).
2. **Before re-exploration.** When you start a new session on a familiar repo,
   read this index first. Re-exploring known territory is the most common token
   waste.

Rules:

- One file per genuine learning. Do not duplicate.
- Verify a recalled fact against current state before acting on it.
- Index entries are one line, under ~150 characters. Keep them scannable.

Buckets:

- `memory/user/` — preferences, profile facts, corrections to remember across sessions
- `memory/feedback/` — session logs, prune reports, validated approaches, router suggestions
- `memory/project/` — per-project decisions, schemas, gotchas, Live State
- `memory/reference/` — external system pointers (dashboards, repos, tools, patterns)
